HEADWORD: Soken
<hw>Sok"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Socome</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A toll. See <er>Soc</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>, 2.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Great <qex>sooken</qex> had this miller, out of doubt.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A district held by socage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soko</ent>⟦br⟧
